2. **Off-by-one resource index** — the `require_once` access `$resource_path` without verifying `$path` has at least 3 elements (index `[2]`). When `$path` has only 2 elements (e.g. `inc/settings`), `$path[2]` is undefined and `trim( strtolower( $path[2] ) )` produces an empty string — the file name ends up as `trait-` or `class-` with no suffix.

3. **Unreachable `default` branch** — because `search-engine` also lacks a `break` (see [1] above), execution always reaches the `default` branch regardless of which case matched. The `search-engine` and `default` branches are effectively merged.

